  "prompt": "Which laptop should I buy under 60000?",
  "response": "Selecting a laptop under \u20b960,000 can depend on your specific needs, such as performance requirements, brand preference, and use cases (e.g., gaming, productivity, multimedia). Here are some good options to consider:\n\n1. **Dell Inspiron 14 (5406)**\n   - Intel Core i5-1135G7 processor\n   - 8GB DDR4 RAM\n   - 512GB SSD\n   - 14-inch Full HD display\n   - Integrated Intel Iris Xe graphics\n\n2. **HP Pavilion x360**\n   - Intel Core i5-1035G1 processor\n   - 8GB DDR4 RAM\n   - 256GB SSD + 1TB HDD\n   - 14-inch Full HD touchscreen display\n   - Integrated Intel UHD graphics\n\n3. **Lenovo IdeaPad Slim 3i**\n   - Intel Core i5-10210U processor\n   - 8GB DDR4 RAM\n   - 512GB SSD\n   - 15.6-inch Full HD display\n   - Integrated Intel UHD graphics\n\n4. **Acer Aspire 7**\n   - AMD Ryzen 5 3550H processor\n   - 8GB DDR4 RAM\n   - 512GB SSD\n   - 15.6-inch Full HD display\n   - NVIDIA GTX 1650 graphics\n\n5. **Asus VivoBook 15**\n   - Intel Core i5-1135G7 processor\n   - 8GB DDR4 RAM\n   - 512GB SSD\n   - 15.6-inch Full HD display\n   - Integrated Intel Iris Xe graphics\n\nWhen choosing, consider what you use your laptop for:\n\n- **For Gaming**: Acer Aspire 7 with NVIDIA GTX 1650 graphics is a good choice.\n- **For Everyday Use**: Dell Inspiron 14 and Lenovo IdeaPad Slim 3i offer solid performance.\n- **For Portability & Flexibility**: HP Pavilion x360 and Asus VivoBook 15 are good for those who want a lighter, touchscreen experience.\n\nAlways check for deals and reviews to get the best possible option within your budget.",
